title: Ridgedale-Carey football preview
text:
Ridgedale Rockets vs. Carey Blue Devils 
Where: Carey High School 
Records: Ridgedale 0-6 overall, 0-4 Northern 10 Conference; Carey 2-4 overall, 1-3 N10 
Last year: Carey won 62-0 
Last week: Ridgedale lost to Colonel Crawford 55-0; Carey defeated Buckeye Central 32-26 
Keys for Carey 
Don’t look beyond Ridgedale team which would like nothing better than to score win No. 1 in this contest. 
Open up holes for RB Jonathon Racheter, who burned Buckeye Central last week for 120 rushing yards. 
Use resiliency it showed last week to beat Buckeye Central in the closing seconds after seeing a 20-0 lead evaporate. 
Keys for Ridgedale 
Rockets hoping to catch Blue Devils in a celebratory mood after their upset of Buckeye Central. 
All the Rockets’ hard work could pay off this week against a two-win Carey squad. 
Ridgedale, shut out the last two weeks, has to produce on offense and do it early against Blue Devils. 
Stat of the week 
Carey scored 32 points last week against a good Buckeye Central team. In three previous weeks, Blue Devils tallied only 30 points combined. Read or Share this story: http://ohne.ws/1RtMoXc More Stories
